        <h4><i>Site News</i></h4>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-04-26</small></span>
            <h5>XMPP notifications</h5>
            <p>Now you can setup your agent to notify via instant messaging, using the XMPP protocol (Jabber, Google Talk etc.).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-03-26</small></span>
            <h5>API available</h5>
            <p>Starting immediately you can manage your agents also via the RESTful API.</p>
            <a href="/apidoc/">Read more</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-24</small></span>
            <h5>Withdrawal notifications</h5>
            <p>Feeling paranoid about your offline paper-wallet long-term savings account? You can now configure your
                agent also to notify if a withdrawal from your address occurs!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-22</small></span>
            <h5>Atom/RSS feeds available</h5>
            <p>A first implementation for Atom and RSS feeds is now available. When you enable <i>Atom/Rss feed notification</i>
            you will see links to the feeds in your dashboard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-19</small></span>
            <h5>Documentation added</h5>
            <p>Today we expanded the support section to provide detailed information about usage of the http callback
            feature. </p>
            <a href="/help/">Read more</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-15</small></span>
            <h5>P2SH support</h5>
            <p>Today our branch of bitcoind was rebased to 0.6.0rc1, fixing issues with P2SH transactions
            which were not recognized correctly with the old 0.5.1-based daemon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-09</small></span>
            <h5>Url callback</h5>
            <p>Secure url callback notifications are now available.</p>
            <a href="/services/#payment">Read more</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ym-clearfix">
            <span class="float-right"><small>2012-02-01</small></span>
            <h5>Hello World!</h5>
            <p>Today, on February 1st 2012, bitcoinmonitor.net is online for the first time
                ever! Let's celebrate :-)</p>
